other_tests.findings: Histologic examination revealed a perifollicular granulomatous and mixed inflammatory infiltrate that included neutrophils and eosinophils. No organisms were seen on periodic acid–Schiff staining, Gram’s staining, or staining for acid-fast bacilli.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The biopsy specimen from the left side of the chin was reviewed at this hospital, and it had previously revealed a granulomatous dermal infiltrate composed of macrophages and scattered giant cells arranged in loose clusters.

other_tests.procedure_name: Interferon-γ release assay for Mycobacterium tuberculosis
